// Regression: a bare `return` (no value) inside `fn main()` compiled `main` as
// `long long wyn_main()` and emitted `return ;` → C error "non-void function
// should return a value". Now a bare return in a non-void fn emits `return 0;`. (2026-07)
fn main() {
    var x = 5
    if x > 3 {
        println("big")
        return
    }
    println("small")
}
// EXPECT: big
